rabbit
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:(esp. as rabbiting verbal noun) (in rugby) carry a grounded ball illegally over the try line
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: does this come from an early cit ?1905 ?1910] Johnny Johnson saw what I did ... that Williams had rabbited the ball across the goalline.
